{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fe47c831-35c5-4995-99f2-1d6692be3b6c","content":"The `dump-collect` skill I have available is for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them. For analyzing your `.dmp` file, here are the recommended tools:\n\n### `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the REPL:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe` | Print last exception (start here!) |\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM crashes) |\n\n### WinDbg (Windows, full-featured)\nLoad the dump, then run `!analyze -v` for automated crash analysis.\n\n### LLDB (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\nWould you like me to walk you through running `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"23400355-1606-4aa1-8550-ce4db6944b95","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo I should not invoke that skill. Instead, I should guide the user on how to analyze the dump file themselves.\n\nLet me provide guidance on analyzing .NET crash dumps using tools like `dotnet-dump analyze`, WinDbg, or lldb.","outputTokens":443,"requestId":"6088:3FDA7D:10D9144:1547BE5:69FFE5B4"},"id":"57ecc076-0c0e-4f89-af7a-121ca6888ef6","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:56:15.769Z","parentId":"560215c7-af59-45f9-9c72-8a981f21e9ac"}
